OL,3,CCumbria councils request delay to
OL,4,Cmayoral election
OL,6,FCumbria's two main councils have
OL,7,Fwritten to the UK Government to
OL,8,Frequest a one-year delay to the
OL,9,Fupcoming mayoral elections.
OL,11,FCumberland Council and Westmorland &
OL,12,FFurness Council have requested that a
OL,13,Fvote be held in May 2027, a year later
OL,14,Fthan planned.
OL,16,FThe government has yet to confirm that
OL,17,Fstatutory tests have been met and that
OL,18,Fdevolution in Cumbria can proceed.
